            "answer_text": "Well\u2026. none. Salt isn\u2019t added to ground beef as a raw ingredient. There might be some trace amounts of salt as the steers would have licked the odd salt block when it was alive.  (from Business Insider[1] ) It\u2019s entirely up to you to decide on how much salt you want in your beef. Now if you meant how much salt was in say a McDonald\u2019s burger or something like that, then that\u2019s different. Footnotes[1] 43,000 pounds of ground beef is being recalled from Walmart and other grocers because of E. coli contamination fears",
